1
00:00:00,900 --> 00:00:03,000
<i>Give me the maps
and I'll let them go.</i>

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:04,467
<i>We're going
to give them to you.</i>

3
00:00:04,700 --> 00:00:07,000
<i> Just let us go!</i>

4
00:00:07,333 --> 00:00:08,667
<i> It's still incomplete!</i>

5
00:00:08,667 --> 00:00:10,667
<i>Your brothers must think
I'm an idiot!</i>

6
00:00:10,667 --> 00:00:12,700
<i> That's all the maps we have!</i>

7
00:00:12,700 --> 00:00:13,700
<i> Liar!</i>

8
00:00:13,700 --> 00:00:15,300
<i> I've changed my mind.</i>

9
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:18,567
<i>Give me the treasure
in 24 hours,</i>

10
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:20,733
<i> or I'll kill them both.</i>

11
00:00:20,733 --> 00:00:22,200
<i> What if Sandro was right?</i>

12
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:23,467
What if there was a fourth map?

13
00:00:23,467 --> 00:00:24,633
<i> But where? How?</i>

14
00:00:24,633 --> 00:00:28,033
<i>If Papa hid a map,
Uncle Fred probably did, too.</i>

15
00:00:28,033 --> 00:00:29,733
<i>That's what
we're going to look for.</i>

16
00:00:29,733 --> 00:00:31,700
<i>Kiko, I know it's hard,
but you have to be strong.</i>

17
00:00:31,700 --> 00:00:33,000
<i> I'm trying my best!</i>

18
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:34,100
<i> Then, try harder.</i>

19
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:35,133
<i> Remember what Papa said?</i>

20
00:00:35,133 --> 00:00:37,533
<i>Only brave boys
find the easter eggs.</i>

21
00:00:37,533 --> 00:00:38,667
<i> Kiko, you're a brave man.</i>

22
00:00:38,667 --> 00:00:40,767
<i> And I know we can find Cheska.</i>

23
00:00:40,767 --> 00:00:42,333
<i> I know we can save them.</i>

24
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:46,700
We've checked all the cabinets
in all the rooms.

25
00:00:47,400 --> 00:00:49,500
We've also checked the garden,
but found nothing.

26
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:51,733
Mom said she didn't find
anything in Dad's office.

27
00:00:52,367 --> 00:00:54,367
We can't stop looking for it.

28
00:00:54,367 --> 00:00:55,700
[JUSTIN] Cheska and Trixie's
lives depend on it.

29
00:00:55,700 --> 00:00:57,067
I know.

30
00:00:57,067 --> 00:00:59,200
But I don't know
where else to look.

31
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,033
I'll go to the hotel
and tell them that

32
00:01:01,033 --> 00:01:02,433
we haven't found anything.

33
00:01:02,433 --> 00:01:04,300
- Jade, you don't have to go--
- No, Luna.

34
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:06,133
It'll give us time to come up
with a backup plan.

35
00:01:06,133 --> 00:01:09,033
Jade, you don't have
to go there. Just call them.

36
00:01:09,067 --> 00:01:10,633
[JADE] I need to go there.

37
00:01:10,633 --> 00:01:13,467
Besides, I also want
to be there for them.

38
00:01:13,467 --> 00:01:14,667
Jade--

39
00:01:14,667 --> 00:01:17,800
[JADE] I will leave and
nothing bad will happen to me.

40
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:19,400
If that's the case,
then I'll come with you.

41
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,533
No, Justin.

42
00:01:20,533 --> 00:01:22,700
Luna and Mom need you here.

43
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:24,300
But my friends are missing.

44
00:01:24,300 --> 00:01:26,767
Help them by not giving up
on your search.

45
00:01:26,767 --> 00:01:31,133
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

46
00:01:31,133 --> 00:01:32,500
I'll get going now.

47
00:01:33,467 --> 00:01:34,567
Jade...

48
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:50,767
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

49
00:02:45,233 --> 00:02:46,600
Gio?

50
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:48,233
Martin?

51
00:02:48,267 --> 00:02:49,267
Kiko?

52
00:02:49,267 --> 00:02:50,400
[GIO] Jade.

53
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:51,533
[JADE] Gio.

54
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:54,467
[GIO] What are you doing here?

55
00:02:54,733 --> 00:02:56,567
Luna said you wouldn't
come here anymore, right?

56
00:02:56,567 --> 00:02:58,900
She can't stop me anymore.

57
00:02:58,900 --> 00:03:02,367
We still haven't found
the fourth map yet.

58
00:03:15,567 --> 00:03:17,333
[GIO] He's losing hope already.

59
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:22,767
I can't blame him.
His sister is missing.

60
00:03:25,900 --> 00:03:27,467
I'm just going to talk to him.

61
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:32,300
[KIKO SIGHS DEEPLY]

62
00:03:33,267 --> 00:03:34,367
[JADE] Kiko?

63
00:03:37,233 --> 00:03:38,367
How are you?

64
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:41,967
Have you found anything?

65
00:03:41,967 --> 00:03:45,567
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

66
00:03:45,567 --> 00:03:48,967
But Luna and Justin are
continuously searching.

67
00:03:48,967 --> 00:03:50,400
There's no more time, Jade.

68
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:52,367
What are you talking about?

69
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:54,567
For the first time in my life,

70
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:56,433
I truly felt like
I couldn't do anything.

71
00:03:56,433 --> 00:03:58,667
Sandro will kill them tomorrow.

72
00:03:58,667 --> 00:04:00,500
My sister will die, Jade.

73
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:02,267
[JADE] Can you hear
what you're saying?

74
00:04:02,267 --> 00:04:03,500
I can't do anything!

75
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:05,667
We only have less than
24 hours left.

76
00:04:05,667 --> 00:04:07,233
Get a hold of yourself!

77
00:04:07,967 --> 00:04:10,567
[WHIMPERS] I'm done, Jade.
I feel scared.

78
00:04:10,567 --> 00:04:12,567
[JADE] That's not the Kiko
I know.

79
00:04:12,567 --> 00:04:16,700
The Kiko I know never
gives up no matter what.

80
00:04:16,967 --> 00:04:20,333
The Kiko I know
will fight to the end.

81
00:04:20,333 --> 00:04:23,967
Kiko, I've also lost a father
and a sibling to that man.

82
00:04:23,967 --> 00:04:26,567
But Cheska's still alive.

83
00:04:26,567 --> 00:04:27,567
She's alive, Kiko!

84
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:30,000
And unless you see her corpse,

85
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:32,433
she's still alive and
you'll fight for her.

86
00:04:32,433 --> 00:04:37,000
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

87
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:40,400
I'm used to living
with hardships.

88
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:46,867
But I could only handle it
because of Mama and Cheska.

89
00:04:49,567 --> 00:04:51,733
Now that one of them
is in danger, Jade,

90
00:04:51,733 --> 00:04:54,700
I don't know what to do.
I hope he just took me instead.

91
00:04:55,733 --> 00:04:59,267
We may not have been able
to bring Leon and Monette home,

92
00:04:59,267 --> 00:05:01,867
but we're going to bring
Cheska home, okay?

93
00:05:02,767 --> 00:05:06,067
We'll bring her home.
Do you understand me, Kiko?

94
00:05:06,067 --> 00:05:09,400
Cheska, Trixie...

95
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:14,433
None of our siblings
will die anymore.

96
00:05:14,433 --> 00:05:21,400
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

97
00:05:22,067 --> 00:05:23,633
Okay?

98
00:05:26,667 --> 00:05:28,033
[SNIFFLES]

99
00:05:36,433 --> 00:05:43,400
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

100
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,933
[BOTONG] Are you coming
home now?

101
00:05:48,933 --> 00:05:51,733
Yes, Grandpa. I'm just
waiting for a boat now.

102
00:05:53,833 --> 00:05:55,633
[BOTONG] How's Martin doing?

103
00:05:57,600 --> 00:06:00,400
Well, he's still
not doing good, Grandpa.

104
00:06:01,433 --> 00:06:02,833
Grandpa, could you...

105
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:06,400
see where Cheska and
Trixie are right now?

106
00:06:07,867 --> 00:06:09,700
[BOTONG SIGHS DEEPLY]

107
00:06:09,700 --> 00:06:10,833
Grandpa...

108
00:06:11,367 --> 00:06:13,000
Just say it.

109
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:16,833
I know that sigh.
I know you can see something.

110
00:06:16,833 --> 00:06:18,700
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

111
00:06:18,700 --> 00:06:21,400
[BOTONG]
<i> They're just close, dear.</i>

112
00:06:24,367 --> 00:06:26,733
[BOTONG] They're not that far.

113
00:06:33,667 --> 00:06:40,667
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

114
00:06:40,700 --> 00:06:47,667
[PAPER RUSTLING]

115
00:06:48,867 --> 00:06:49,867
[GUN COCKS]

116
00:06:49,867 --> 00:06:52,467
[CHESKA] What's that?
What are you doing?

117
00:06:52,467 --> 00:06:54,833
What are you planning?
[WHIMPERS]

118
00:06:55,933 --> 00:07:00,733
What's that? What are you doing?
What are you planning to do?

119
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:03,800
I'm looking for another way.

120
00:07:04,833 --> 00:07:10,800
If your families won't
give me what I need...

121
00:07:12,433 --> 00:07:14,600
then I'll approach
another family.

122
00:07:14,633 --> 00:07:15,800
What?

123
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:17,633
What? What family?

124
00:07:17,633 --> 00:07:20,767
What family? Who? What?

125
00:07:20,767 --> 00:07:23,167
Why should you care, huh?

126
00:07:23,167 --> 00:07:25,733
- [CHAIR SHAKING]
- You have too many questions.

127
00:07:26,467 --> 00:07:27,500
Wait!

128
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:29,767
Wait a minute, 24 hours
haven't passed yet!

129
00:07:29,767 --> 00:07:31,933
They will give you
everything you want.

130
00:07:31,933 --> 00:07:34,733
Just wait, please.

131
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:38,500
If they wanted
to give it to me...

132
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,833
they would've given it already.

133
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:45,700
[CRYING] They haven't
found it yet!

134
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:49,667
They haven't seen it yet,
so wait!

135
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:50,800
[CHESKA] Just wait.

136
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:53,833
Do you really think that
they haven't found it yet?

137
00:07:54,867 --> 00:07:56,000
Huh?

138
00:07:56,633 --> 00:07:58,633
Do you really believe that?

139
00:07:58,633 --> 00:08:01,033
[SOBBING]

140
00:08:01,033 --> 00:08:04,467
[SANDRO] They won't give
the treasure to me.

141
00:08:04,467 --> 00:08:07,833
- They'll give it to you!
- Remember this.

142
00:08:08,633 --> 00:08:12,967
Money changes people.

143
00:08:14,467 --> 00:08:15,833
The treasure can do that.

144
00:08:16,033 --> 00:08:18,700
- [CHESKA CRYING]
- No...

145
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:20,667
[SANDRO] You may have
thought that...

146
00:08:21,633 --> 00:08:24,000
your families would choose you.

147
00:08:26,133 --> 00:08:28,233
But they didn't!

148
00:08:28,700 --> 00:08:32,100
That's not the truth.
That's not true.

149
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:33,700
That's not true!

150
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:37,100
- No! No! No!
- [TRIXIE WAILING] No!

151
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:39,267
[BOMB TICKING]

152
00:08:39,267 --> 00:08:41,267
- No!
- Don't leave us here!

153
00:08:41,267 --> 00:08:43,267
[TRIXIE] Let us go, please!

154
00:08:43,267 --> 00:08:46,233
- No!
- No!

155
00:08:46,867 --> 00:08:48,867
Please help us!

156
00:08:48,867 --> 00:08:52,833
- [WAILING] No!
- Help!

157
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,133
Trixie...

158
00:08:55,900 --> 00:08:57,900
Help!

159
00:08:57,900 --> 00:09:04,833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

160
00:09:05,267 --> 00:09:07,833
Grandpa said they're close by.

161
00:09:08,867 --> 00:09:10,833
That means they're
just around here.

162
00:09:13,267 --> 00:09:16,267
I also have a feeling that
it's just around here.

163
00:09:16,267 --> 00:09:23,233
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

164
00:09:38,300 --> 00:09:44,867
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

165
00:09:44,867 --> 00:09:46,233
Sari...

166
00:09:46,867 --> 00:09:48,233
Sari.

167
00:09:48,867 --> 00:09:50,833
That's just your imagination,
Sari.

168
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:53,267
You have to help them.

169
00:09:53,267 --> 00:09:55,633
They need your help, okay?

170
00:09:55,633 --> 00:09:57,267
That was just your imagination.

171
00:09:57,267 --> 00:10:02,867
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

172
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:04,033
Who's there?

173
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:09,267
[SARI] Sir Martin?

174
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:11,867
Sir Martin, is that you?

175
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:19,733
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

176
00:10:19,733 --> 00:10:21,033
[SARI] Who's there?

177
00:10:24,133 --> 00:10:25,700
Sir Martin?

178
00:10:30,633 --> 00:10:32,000
Sir Martin?

179
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:41,967
- [SARI SCREAMING]
- [SANDRO GROANING IN PAIN]

180
00:10:41,967 --> 00:10:45,833
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

181
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:50,033
- [LINE RINGING]
- Why isn't he answering?

182
00:10:50,033 --> 00:10:51,667
We've got five hours left.

183
00:10:51,667 --> 00:10:53,500
Luna still hasn't found
anything.

184
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:54,633
I even called Andy.

185
00:10:54,633 --> 00:10:57,100
I practically begged him
to tell me where Sandro is.

186
00:10:57,633 --> 00:10:59,567
But he insists he doesn't know.

187
00:10:59,567 --> 00:11:01,667
Maybe he really has nothing
to do with this.

188
00:11:01,667 --> 00:11:03,133
[PHONE RINGING]

189
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,200
Sandro?

190
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:07,467
- [RINGING CONTINUES]
- It's Sari.

191
00:11:09,167 --> 00:11:10,467
Hello, Sari?

192
00:11:11,367 --> 00:11:13,700
Sir Martin!
Sir Martin!

193
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:15,667
I found what you're looking for!

194
00:11:15,667 --> 00:11:17,067
Sandro!

195
00:11:17,067 --> 00:11:18,467
<i> He's here in the forest!</i>

196
00:11:18,467 --> 00:11:20,300
What?
How did you find him?

197
00:11:22,133 --> 00:11:24,100
Sir, he's chasing me right now!

198
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:26,167
[SCREAMING] Sir!

199
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:28,233
Sir, he's here!

200
00:11:28,233 --> 00:11:29,367
[MARTIN] Sari!

201
00:11:29,367 --> 00:11:31,467
- Sari!
- Martin, what did Sari say?

202
00:11:31,467 --> 00:11:32,633
Sandro's chasing her.

203
00:11:32,633 --> 00:11:34,200
- Let's go!
- She's in danger!

204
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:44,533
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

205
00:11:44,567 --> 00:11:46,600
[JADE] Because of the treasure,

206
00:11:47,467 --> 00:11:49,367
<i> I lost my father.</i>

207
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:52,000
<i> Monette...</i>

208
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:55,667
<i> and my brother, Leon.</i>

209
00:11:55,667 --> 00:11:58,233
I hope it doesn't happen again.

210
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:03,733
[EDWARD]<i> You've already lost
</i> so many people in your life.

211
00:12:04,467 --> 00:12:06,100
<i> But you're still so strong.</i>

212
00:12:07,300 --> 00:12:10,267
<i>Unlike me, I'm stuck
dealing with my dad.</i>

213
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:16,400
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

214
00:12:17,233 --> 00:12:19,367
<i> Dad, let's meet.</i>

215
00:12:20,267 --> 00:12:22,667
Let's talk. I'm coming home now.

216
00:12:24,233 --> 00:12:27,433
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

217
00:12:27,433 --> 00:12:28,533
[MUSIC FADES]

218
00:12:28,533 --> 00:12:31,700
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

219
00:12:32,233 --> 00:12:35,133
[SANDRO GROANS]

220
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:36,667
[SCREAMING]

221
00:12:37,267 --> 00:12:38,400
Come out!

222
00:12:41,167 --> 00:12:42,267
Come out!

223
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:45,233
I know you're there!

224
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:48,700
[SCREAMING]

225
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:58,167
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

226
00:12:58,167 --> 00:12:59,600
I can see you!

227
00:13:01,700 --> 00:13:08,667
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

228
00:13:10,067 --> 00:13:11,300
Sari!

229
00:13:11,300 --> 00:13:12,833
Kiko, what did Raphie say?

230
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:15,833
He didn't pass that CCTV area.

231
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:18,400
There's cameras everywhere,
and he didn't show up?

232
00:13:21,533 --> 00:13:23,100
He really couldn't be seen.

233
00:13:25,733 --> 00:13:28,133
Someone already changed
the camera positions.

234
00:13:28,667 --> 00:13:34,567
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

235
00:13:35,333 --> 00:13:36,333
That bastard knows

236
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:38,400
exactly where you placed
the cameras, Martin.

237
00:13:40,533 --> 00:13:42,800
[SANDRO] I can see you.

238
00:13:47,300 --> 00:13:49,200
Come out.

239
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:53,300
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

240
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:54,333
[SCREAMS]

241
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:03,833
[SOBBING]

242
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:10,533
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

243
00:14:10,533 --> 00:14:15,400
If I catch you, you're dead.

244
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:17,867
[SINISTER LAUGH]

245
00:14:17,867 --> 00:14:22,533
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

246
00:14:22,533 --> 00:14:29,533
[SARI SOBBING]

247
00:14:29,567 --> 00:14:36,567
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

248
00:14:38,867 --> 00:14:43,767
[SOBBING]

249
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:45,933
[MARTIN] Sari!

250
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,233
Sari!

251
00:14:51,467 --> 00:14:53,000
Sir Martin? [GASPS]

252
00:14:55,267 --> 00:14:56,267
Sari?

253
00:14:56,267 --> 00:14:57,533
- [SARI] Sir Martin!
- Sari.

254
00:14:57,533 --> 00:14:58,567
Sir Martin!

255
00:14:58,567 --> 00:15:03,267
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

256
00:15:03,300 --> 00:15:04,267
[SARI SOBS]

257
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:07,233
[SOBS, CRIES]

258
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:11,967
Hey...

259
00:15:12,533 --> 00:15:14,333
- [SARI SOBS, CRIES]
- Sari...

260
00:15:14,333 --> 00:15:16,100
[SARI BREATH QUIVERS]

261
00:15:16,100 --> 00:15:17,567
- Sari...
- [SOBS]

262
00:15:19,567 --> 00:15:20,867
Are you okay?

263
00:15:22,233 --> 00:15:23,267
[SNIFFLES]

264
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:25,933
Yes.

265
00:15:26,633 --> 00:15:30,067
Sir, the Sandro
you're looking for

266
00:15:30,067 --> 00:15:31,933
is just here at Hotel 88.

267
00:15:31,933 --> 00:15:34,333
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

268
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:36,167
Sir, he's not leaving.

269
00:15:42,167 --> 00:15:44,367
We need to inform the police.

270
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,367
We need them now.

271
00:15:48,067 --> 00:15:49,500
Mama has been wanting
to report this for a long time.

272
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:50,567
I'll let her.

273
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,367
Okay.

274
00:15:52,667 --> 00:15:54,633
Let's get out of here.
We're not safe here.

275
00:15:54,633 --> 00:15:56,500
Let's go.

276
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:01,300
They've been missing
since yesterday?

277
00:16:02,433 --> 00:16:03,467
Yes, sir.

278
00:16:04,067 --> 00:16:07,467
Sandro threatened them.

279
00:16:08,167 --> 00:16:12,433
He said he would kill
Trixie and Cheska

280
00:16:12,433 --> 00:16:14,200
if they reported it.

281
00:16:15,533 --> 00:16:16,967
We've been looking for him

282
00:16:16,967 --> 00:16:19,167
since what happened
to Kiko and Leon.

283
00:16:19,167 --> 00:16:21,067
My men are already spread out.

284
00:16:21,067 --> 00:16:22,433
Sir... [SOBS]

285
00:16:22,700 --> 00:16:24,600
I'm pleading.

286
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,700
I'm begging you.

287
00:16:26,700 --> 00:16:29,567
Please don't let
our children die.

288
00:16:29,567 --> 00:16:31,133
Please, sir.

289
00:16:31,133 --> 00:16:33,500
Help us. Please have mercy.

290
00:16:34,967 --> 00:16:36,000
Okay.

291
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:36,967
Excuse me.

292
00:16:42,233 --> 00:16:43,633
Alert all units.

293
00:16:44,467 --> 00:16:46,467
Escalate the manhunt
for Sandro Soliman.

294
00:16:46,467 --> 00:16:48,100
Lock down all exits.

295
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:50,667
Activate CCTV backtracking.

296
00:16:51,267 --> 00:16:52,700
This is a priority target.

297
00:16:52,700 --> 00:16:53,967
- [OFFICER 1] Copy, sir.
- OFFICER 2] Copy.

298
00:16:53,967 --> 00:17:00,700
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

299
00:17:13,300 --> 00:17:17,067
[EDWARD MUFFLED GROANING]

300
00:17:17,100 --> 00:17:20,000
[TENSE MUSIC SWELLS]

301
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:21,600
- Edward?
- [EDWARD MUFFLED GROAN]

302
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:22,733
- Edward!
- [HACK SWISH]

303
00:17:24,433 --> 00:17:26,667
Give me your map

304
00:17:26,667 --> 00:17:29,100
if you want your son to live.

305
00:17:29,100 --> 00:17:30,200
[MUFFLED GROANS]

306
00:17:30,600 --> 00:17:33,067
Please, don't hurt Edward.
Please.

307
00:17:33,633 --> 00:17:35,633
Give me the map.

308
00:17:37,667 --> 00:17:39,233
I'll give you the map.

309
00:17:39,233 --> 00:17:40,400
It's in here.

310
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:43,467
But please,
please don't hurt Edward.

311
00:17:43,467 --> 00:17:45,600
[MUFFLED GROANING]

312
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:47,533
[ANDY] Please, Sandro,
don't hurt Edward.

313
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:50,633
I'll give it to you.
It's here.

314
00:17:50,633 --> 00:17:54,267
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

315
00:17:54,267 --> 00:17:55,767
Here. Here.

316
00:18:02,133 --> 00:18:04,100
I already have this.

317
00:18:05,133 --> 00:18:08,267
All of you are fooling me!

318
00:18:08,267 --> 00:18:09,533
I'm not fooling you!

319
00:18:11,167 --> 00:18:12,633
Get it from Michael's sons,

320
00:18:12,633 --> 00:18:13,767
they have a map!

321
00:18:14,300 --> 00:18:16,067
They gave it to me,
but it's incomplete!

322
00:18:16,067 --> 00:18:17,533
- You have the other one!
- I don't have it!

323
00:18:17,533 --> 00:18:19,267
That's all I have!

324
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:24,767
Get it from them if you still
want to see your son alive!

325
00:18:24,767 --> 00:18:26,133
It's with the Almazans.

326
00:18:26,833 --> 00:18:29,133
- It's with the Almazans.
- [MUFFLED GROAN]

327
00:18:29,133 --> 00:18:31,200
If it's not with
Michael's children,

328
00:18:31,200 --> 00:18:32,700
it's definitely
with the Almazans.

329
00:18:33,667 --> 00:18:37,767
Get the map from them if you
still want your child alive!

330
00:18:39,233 --> 00:18:41,033
[BREATHES HEAVILY]
Okay...

331
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:42,800
Okay.

332
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:47,433
[ANDY] Don't hurt Edward.

333
00:18:48,167 --> 00:18:50,367
- Get it!
- Don't hurt...

334
00:18:50,367 --> 00:18:51,400
...Edward!

335
00:18:51,833 --> 00:18:53,100
Edward!

336
00:18:53,667 --> 00:18:55,533
I'll be back, okay!

337
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:57,633
I'll be back.

338
00:18:58,733 --> 00:19:00,700
Sandro, don't hurt Edward.

339
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:07,633
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

340
00:19:16,867 --> 00:19:23,833
[SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

341
00:19:26,133 --> 00:19:27,267
Dad?

342
00:19:28,633 --> 00:19:30,533
Are you with Leon up there?

343
00:19:33,667 --> 00:19:35,333
I'm scared, Dad.

344
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:38,867
I wish you were here.

345
00:19:42,867 --> 00:19:44,867
[FEDERICO] Dear, it's okay.

346
00:19:45,633 --> 00:19:48,267
<i> Daddy's here, okay?</i>

347
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:49,867
<i> Everything will be okay.</i>

348
00:19:49,867 --> 00:19:51,200
[LUNA SNIFFLES, CRIES]

349
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:52,200
<i> Hmm?</i>

350
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:55,400
[MUSIC BOX CRANKS]

351
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:58,800
[DISCORDANT PIANO MUSIC PLAYING]

352
00:20:06,367 --> 00:20:13,367
[MUSIC TURNS PENSIVE]

353
00:20:15,167 --> 00:20:16,533
[MUSIC BOX CRANKS]

354
00:20:17,367 --> 00:20:21,867
[DISCORDANT PIANO MUSIC PLAYS]

355
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:36,733
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

356
00:20:42,300 --> 00:20:43,467
A map?

357
00:20:53,700 --> 00:20:54,833
Luna...

358
00:20:55,633 --> 00:20:56,800
Jade, Justin.

359
00:20:57,333 --> 00:20:58,300
Look at this.

360
00:20:58,300 --> 00:20:59,333
What is it?

361
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:01,367
Luna!

362
00:21:03,567 --> 00:21:04,633
Luna...

363
00:21:05,233 --> 00:21:07,167
that's the last piece.

364
00:21:07,567 --> 00:21:09,167
You found it.

365
00:21:10,900 --> 00:21:12,833
We'll be able
to save my friends!

366
00:21:13,867 --> 00:21:15,467
Let's give it to the others.

367
00:21:16,733 --> 00:21:17,733
"Us"?

368
00:21:18,367 --> 00:21:19,567
Including me?

369
00:21:20,333 --> 00:21:21,900
Yes, of course!

370
00:21:22,333 --> 00:21:23,467
Don't be scared.

371
00:21:23,467 --> 00:21:24,600
Go out.

372
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:26,467
Let's give this to Kiko.
They need it.

373
00:21:26,733 --> 00:21:27,700
But...

374
00:21:29,367 --> 00:21:32,267
It's painful to lose a sibling.

375
00:21:35,367 --> 00:21:37,267
Let's not let them feel
the same way.

376
00:21:40,933 --> 00:21:42,667
- Come on.
- Let's go.

377
00:21:45,767 --> 00:21:46,900
Come on.

378
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:49,367
- Okay.
- [CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

379
00:21:49,633 --> 00:21:51,333
Okay.

380
00:21:54,433 --> 00:21:56,800
Sir, where are you going?
Wait a minute!

381
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:58,800
- Let go!
- Sir!

382
00:22:01,367 --> 00:22:03,600
Get your hands off me!

383
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:04,800
Andy!

384
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:06,967
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

385
00:22:06,967 --> 00:22:09,467
What are you doing?
You're not welcome here!

386
00:22:09,467 --> 00:22:11,333
- Just go!
- Please, give me the map!

387
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:12,733
Please. Just give me the map.

388
00:22:12,733 --> 00:22:15,633
I don't know
what you're talking about.

389
00:22:16,933 --> 00:22:18,533
- Mom!
- Where's the map?

390
00:22:18,533 --> 00:22:20,300
- Give me the map!
- M-map?

391
00:22:20,300 --> 00:22:21,867
- Uncle...
- We don't have it!

392
00:22:22,433 --> 00:22:25,000
Andy, you won't get
a map from them

393
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,900
because we've also
been searching for it

394
00:22:26,900 --> 00:22:28,867
to no avail!

395
00:22:30,633 --> 00:22:32,400
Don't lie to me!

396
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:33,533
Stop, Uncle!

397
00:22:33,533 --> 00:22:35,333
I know you have it!

398
00:22:35,700 --> 00:22:36,933
I know you have it.

399
00:22:36,933 --> 00:22:39,900
Please just give it to me.
I need the map.

400
00:22:39,900 --> 00:22:41,867
Just give it. Give it to me.

401
00:22:41,867 --> 00:22:48,833
[MUSIC BUILDS]

402
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:51,433
<i> Remember what Papa said?</i>

403
00:22:51,433 --> 00:22:53,400
<i>That the treasure
is within Hotel 88?</i>

404
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:56,733
<i>But these four locations,
Kiko, are not in Hotel 88.</i>

405
00:22:56,733 --> 00:22:59,367
<i>Four locations,
but none in the hotel.</i>

406
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:01,333
<i> The point of intersection.</i>

407
00:23:01,333 --> 00:23:03,733
What if it wasn't a coincidence
<i> that it's all in Hotel 88?</i>

408
00:23:03,733 --> 00:23:05,767
This might be Sandro's hideout.

409
00:23:05,767 --> 00:23:07,967
<i>So, it's possible that
Trixie and Cheska are here, too!</i>

410
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:09,400
<i> This is it!</i>

411
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:11,033
- [GRUNTS]
- [CRASHES]

412
00:23:11,033 --> 00:23:12,600
- [YELLS]
- [THUDS]

413
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:14,433
<i> Edward, run!</i>

414
00:23:14,433 --> 00:23:15,833
[CHAIN RATTLING]

415
00:23:15,833 --> 00:23:17,400
<i> Hurry, Trixie!</i>

416
00:23:17,633 --> 00:23:18,833
<i> Help!</i>
